p;]\'>Donncha: Fatal error: Allowed memory size of 67108864 bytes exhausted</a></li><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'http://wordpress.org/news/2012/05/calling-all-contributors-community-summit-2012/\' title=\'Each year, the WordPress core development team meets in person for a week to work together and discuss the vision for WordPress in the coming year. As annual events go, it’s easily my favorite. Don’t get me wrong, I love attending WordCamps and local WordPress meetups (which are awesome and you should try to attend if you are able), but at the core team meet [&hellip;]\'>Dev Blog: Calling All Contributors: Community Summit 2012</a></li><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'http://markjaquith.wordpress.com/2012/05/15/how-i-built-have-baby-need-stuff/\' title=\'Have Baby. Need Stuff! is a baby gear site that my wife and I just launched. I thought I’d share how I built it. WordPress Core WordPress is a Git submodule, with the content directory moved to the /content/ directory. This makes my Git repo smaller, as WordPress isn’t actually in it. Underscores For a theme base, I started with the Underscores starter theme [&hellip;]\'>Mark Jaquith: How I built “Have Baby. Need Stuff!”</a></li></ul></div>','no'),(161,0,'theme_mods_twentyeleven','a:1:{s:16:\"sidebars_widgets\";a:2:{s:4:\"time\";i:1337193429;s:4:\"data\";a:6:{s:19:\"wp_inactive_widgets\";a:0:{}s:9:\"sidebar-1\";a:6:{i:0;s:8:\"search-2\";i:1;s:14:\"recent-posts-2\";i:2;s:17:\"recent-comments-2\";i:3;s:10:\"archives-2\";i:4;s:12:\"categories-2\";i:5;s:6:\"meta-2\";}s:9:\"sidebar-2\";a:0:{}s:9:\"sidebar-3\";a:0:{}s:9:\"sidebar-4\";a:0:{}s:9:\"sidebar-5\";a:0:{}}}}','yes'),(162,0,'current_theme','Campanha Padrão','yes'),(163,0,'theme_mods_campanha_padrao','a:10:{i:0;b:0;s:12:\"header_image\";s:63:\"http://andersonorui.campanha.mu/files/2012/05/andersonorui5.png\";s:16:\"header_textcolor\";s:5:\"blank\";s:18:\"nav_menu_locations\";a:2:{s:6:\"menu_1\";i:4;s:6:\"menu_2\";i:3;}s:16:\"background_color\";s:0:\"\";s:16: